race.comment: SUPREME STATEMENT (1) took nine runs but finally broke the maiden status last start over 1350m at the Beaumont circuit. Backs up eight days later and can step up to this level successfully. DOWN THE KOOKA (8) disappointed last time out over the mile at Scone, travelling midfield but failing to improve. Has won here at this distance. Blinkers go on for the first time today so it will be no surprise if he bounced back to form. XERXES (2) bolted in over 1600m at Gunnedah two back to crack the maiden. Failed over a longer journey at Armidale more recently. Yet to miss the placings in three runs here and coming back to a more suitable trip puts him right in contention. PONTEVEDRA (6) chimed in late to get the prize over 1280m here last start when lining up for only the second time. Plenty of scope for further improvement. RASLOC (9) has been about the mark at both runs this prep and is ready to peak.
